  "body": "When clicking on a community channel category, it flickers and also throws the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nERR 2022-07-20 16:15:28.202+02:00 Error reordering category channel          topics=\"community-service\" tid=2599508 file=service.nim:997 msg=\"\\nstatus-go error [methodName:wakuext_reorderCommunityCategories, code:-32000, message:no change in category position ]\\n\"\r\n```\r\nThere's a few issues here:\r\n\r\n1. We shouldn't even try to call `reorderCommunityCategories` when we merely click the category (to toggle it). So something is going on that an actual drag/n'drop event is triggered\r\n2. The flicker happens because, visually, when we drag and drop, we render a half transparent copy of the dragged item. Because the simple click seems to be interpreted as a drag, it shows that \"ghost\" element for a very short period (as long as the click is pressed), which makes it look like it flickers",
